The paper discusses collaborative beamforming in wireless sensor networks, which involves signal processing and communication aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with network transmission and interference, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes a node selection algorithm, which involves optimization and decision-making, indicating the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper uses simulation results to validate the proposed algorithm, which suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the performance analysis of the proposed algorithm, which involves statistical and probabilistic methods, indicating the category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
